# UFree App - Cline AI Context & Rules

## Project Overview & Architecture
- **App:** UFree (iOS Mobile App).
- **Core Features:** Social Graph, Nudges, In-App Notification Center.
- **Data Flow:** UI → ViewModel → CompositeRepository → SwiftData (instant) + Firestore (background).
- **Notifications:** Rely exclusively on in-app state/Firestore. Do NOT implement APNs at this stage.

## Code Style & Standards
- **UI:** SwiftUI ONLY (No UIKit).
- **Concurrency:** Use `async/await` (No Combine). Ensure all UI components and ViewModels are marked with `@MainActor`.
- **State Management:** Use `@Published` for ViewModel state.
- **Protection:** All interactive ViewModels must use `guard !isProcessing` rapid-tap protection.

## File Organization
- **Domain Models:** `UFree/Core/Domain/`
- **Repositories:** `UFree/Core/Data/` (Use Protocol-based repos for testability).
- **ViewModels & Views:** `UFree/Features/*/`
- **Tests:** `UFreeTests/`

## Testing Protocol
- **Rule:** Run tests ONLY if code logic changes. Skip tests for docs/comments.
- **Pattern:** Arrange-Act-Assert.
- **Naming:** `test_[method]_[expectedBehavior]()`
- **Execution Command:** To validate your changes, use this exact command:
  `xcodebuild test -scheme UFreeUnitTests -project UFree.xcodeproj -destination 'platform=iOS Simulator,name=iPhone 17 Pro' 2>&1 | grep -E '(PASS|FAIL|passed|failed|warning)'`

## Deployment & Fastlane
- **Tooling:** Fastlane is the source of truth.
- **Commands:** You are authorized to run `fastlane tests`, `fastlane alpha`, and `fastlane beta` via the terminal to verify builds or deploy.
- **Debugging:** If you encounter Ruby/OpenSSL errors or CI crashes, read the terminal output and fix the Swift concurrency issues or scripts directly.

## Git Commit Convention
- When asked to commit, you MUST analyze the git diff and format the commit message using this exact pattern: `(TYPE) brief description in mostly lowercase`
- **DO NOT** use standard conventional commit syntax (e.g., `feat: message`).
- **Valid Types:** (FEAT), (FIX), (CHORE), (REFACTOR), (TEST), (DOCS).
- **Examples:**
  - `(FEAT) add app icon with single size`
  - `(FIX) crashes on unit test CI for main actor`

## Agent Behavior
- **Pacing:** Execute one logical feature or fix at a time to respect API limits.
- **Verification:** Always aim to verify your changes compile successfully before finalizing the task.

## Terminal & API Limit Protections
- **The Token Explosion Rule:** You are operating under strict API token limits. Massive terminal logs will cause you to hang and timeout.
- **Suppress Output:** Whenever running `fastlane`, `xcodebuild`, `pod install`, or any build commands, you MUST use quiet flags or pipe the output. 
- **Read Errors Smartly:** Never print or read full build logs directly in the terminal. If a build fails and you need to investigate, pipe the output to a temporary `.log` file, and then use `tail -n 50 build.log` or `grep -A 10 "error:" build.log` to read only the relevant failure details.
- **The "Two Strike" Rule:** If a terminal command fails twice in a row, DO NOT attempt a third time. Stop the loop immediately, explain the error to the user, and wait for human guidance.